(Node Stop Utility \(Src/Main/stop.py\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Last refresh: 2026-04-10) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This utility provides a deterministic way to stop Atho node processes, including nodes started) Tj
T*
(from different shells, launch scripts, or background sessions. It is designed for operational) Tj
T*
(safety: match only known Atho process patterns, stop gracefully first, then force-stop only when) Tj
T*
(required.) Tj
T*
(- Why This Utility Exists) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(runnode.py and related launch paths can start multiple long-lived processes. Without a) Tj
T*
(centralized stop mechanism, operators may rely on manual process hunting, which is error-prone) Tj
T*
(and risks killing unrelated Python workloads.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(stop.py addresses this by providing:) Tj
T*
(- role-aware stop actions \(full, miner, wallet, launcher\),) Tj
T*
(- all-node stop behavior,) Tj
T*
(- explicit PID targeting,) Tj
T*
(- list and watch modes for live visibility,) Tj
T*
(- reusable Python-callable functions for API/GUI integration.) Tj
T*
(- Targeted Process Scope) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Default target process names:) Tj
T*
(- fullnode.py) Tj
T*
(- minernode.py) Tj
T*
(- walletnode.py) Tj
T*
(- runminer.py) Tj
T*
(- runnode.py \(launcher\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Scope safety rule:) Tj
T*
(- the tool is intentionally narrow,) Tj
T*
(- it does not terminate arbitrary Python processes,) Tj
T*
(- operator intent is explicit through flags or menu selection.) Tj
T*
(- CLI Usage) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(From repository root:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(No flags opens interactive mode with role-specific options.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Non-interactive examples:) Tj
T*
(- Programmatic API Functions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Importable utilities for integrations:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main callable functions:) Tj
T*
(- discover_node_processes\(include_launcher=True\)) Tj
T*
(- list_node_processes\(include_launcher=True\)) Tj
T*
(- active_nodes_snapshot\(include_launcher=True\)) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
