(- stop_nodes\(target="all", include_launcher=True, timeout_seconds=5.0, force_kill=True,) Tj
T*
(dry_run=False\)) Tj
T*
(- stop_pids\(pids, timeout_seconds=5.0, force_kill=True, dry_run=False\)) Tj
T*
(- Signal Escalation Behavior) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Stop sequence per process:) Tj
T*
(- send SIGTERM,) Tj
T*
(- wait up to timeout \(default 5s\),) Tj
T*
(- if still alive and force-kill enabled, send SIGKILL.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This preserves graceful shutdown opportunities for state flush and log closure while ensuring) Tj
T*
(stuck processes cannot persist indefinitely.) Tj
T*
(- API and GUI Integration) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The same stop logic is used by API/GUI stop routes so user actions can terminate:) Tj
T*
(- processes started by API-managed lifecycle,) Tj
T*
(- processes started manually from other terminals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Active monitoring endpoint:) Tj
T*
(- GET /nodes/active) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Response includes:) Tj
T*
(- counts_by_role,) Tj
T*
(- per-process PID and role grouping,) Tj
T*
(- flattened process views for UI refresh logic.) Tj
T*
(- Operational Recommendations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Production-like usage guidance:) Tj
T*
(- use --list or --active before stop actions when diagnosing incidents,) Tj
T*
(- use --dry-run in scripted environments before enabling destructive mode,) Tj
T*
(- keep force-kill enabled for unattended automation, but record stop outcomes,) Tj
T*
(- verify no pending maintenance operation depends on node liveness before issuing --all.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For service wrappers or orchestrators, call programmatic functions directly and capture) Tj
T*
(JSON-style result payloads in logs.) Tj
T*
(- Policy Context) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The stop utility itself does not change consensus policy. It supports safe operations around the) Tj
T*
(active production constants:) Tj
T*
(- block cadence 120s,) Tj
T*
(- tx confirmations 10, private tx confirmations 10,) Tj
T*
(- coinbase maturity 150,) Tj
T*
(- fee floor 350 atoms/vB.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Reliable process lifecycle control is part of maintaining operational consistency for these) Tj
T*
(policy-governed runtimes.) Tj
T*
(- Failure and Recovery Notes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If a stop operation appears incomplete:) Tj
T*
(- rerun --list to confirm remaining PID\(s\),) Tj
T*
(- run targeted --pid stop for survivors,) Tj
T*
(- inspect runtime logs for shutdown deadlocks,) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
